'''Grande-Clairi<U+00E8>re''' is an unincorporated settlement in southwestern [[Manitoba]], [[Canada]]. It is located approximately 13 kilometers (8 miles) northwest of [[Hartney, Manitoba]]<ref>http://www.nrcan.gc.ca/earth-sciences/search/calculate_distance_3_e.php?unique_id_str_1=GAJQA&unique_id_str_2=GAKKP</ref> in the [[Cameron, Manitoba (rural municipality)|Rural Municipality of Cameron]].  The community was founded by French and Belgian settlers in 1890.<ref>http://esask.uregina.ca/entry/french_settlements.html</ref>

